%20(22).jpeg 640w\" sizes=\"100vw\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"upc_undefined\" type=\"embed\"\u003eAnnie Selke Classic Hemstitch Bed Skirt\u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003ePopular in the ’80s, the \u003ca href=\"https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/best-bed-skirts\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ebed skirt\u003c/a\u003e is often dismissed as outdated. But this 100% cotton design is graceful and all grown-up, featuring split corners, decorative stitching, and a tidy silhouette.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
